Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Finely chop the @chives{½%bunch} (use scissors if easier). Trim the @green beans{150%g}.

Put a large #saucepan{} of water with 1/4 tsp @salt{} on to boil for the potatoes. Put half the @chicken stock paste{10%g} in a #measuring jug{} and pour in the @boiled water{100%ml} for the stock from your kettle - this is your chicken stock.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the @butter{30%g} and onion. Season with salt and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{3%minutes}.

Pour in your chicken stock and stir to combine, then transfer everything to an #ovenproof dish{} and set aside.

Wipe out the (now empty) #frying pan{} and pop on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, lay the @skin-on British chicken breasts{2} into the pan, skin-side down. Season with salt and pepper.

Fry until the skin is golden, ~{5-6%minutes}, then turn and cook for ~{1%minute} on the other side.

Transfer the chicken to the #ovenproof dish{}, skin-side up, then bake on the top shelf of your oven until cooked, ~{18-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the chicken is cooked, remove from your oven and leave to rest for a couple of mins.

Meanwhile, add the potatoes to your pan of boiling water and cook until you can easily slip a #knife{} through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the saucepan, off the heat. Add the chives, a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{} and mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}.

Season with salt and pepper. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in the now empty frying pan on medium-high heat. Once the pan is hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash of @water{} and immediately cover with a lid or some #foil{}. Cook until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Season with salt and pepper. Remove the pan from the heat. Transfer the beans to a #medium bowl{} and cover with a lid or foil to keep warm.

Add the @apple and sage jelly{50%g} to the now empty frying pan and warm through on low heat.

Stir in the remaining chicken stock paste and the @water for the glaze{50%ml}. Bring to the boil and allow to bubble for ~{30%seconds}, then remove from the heat.

When everything's ready, share the chive mash between your plates and serve the buttered onions and green beans alongside (discard any excess liquid).

Top with the chicken and spoon over the apple and sage jelly glaze to finish. Enjoy!